THE Confederations of African Football (CAF) has changed the date of the draw for the 2019 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations. It has been brought forward a day earlier. It was scheduled for Thursday, 3 October but will now take place on Wednesday, 2 October 2019, in Alexandria (5pm SA Time). The decision was taken in consultation with the Local Organising Committee (LOC) due to logistical reasons. The eight teams who are the host Egypt, Cameroon, Cote d’Ivoire, Ghana, Mali, Nigeria, South Africa and Zambia will know their opponents at the iconic 19th century palace. The representatives of the qualified teams are expected to be in attendance for the event, with the tournament scheduled on the 8-22 November 2019. From Safa’s side, U-23 coach David Notoane will be in attendance. Cairo will be the centre of attention during the event as it will host all games. The giant Cairo International Stadium and Al Salam Stadium are venues that will be used.In this tournament, the best three finishers will qualify to represent Africa at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. However, the team that finished fourth it will not all over for them either. They will face the nation from Asia in the two-legged tie. 